com.percussion.cms.objectstore
Class PSActiveAssemblyProcessorProxy

java.lang.Object
  com.percussion.cms.objectstore.PSProcessorProxy
      com.percussion.cms.objectstore.PSActiveAssemblyProcessorProxy

public class PSActiveAssemblyProcessorProxy
extends PSProcessorProxy

This class extends PSProcessorProxy and is to manipulate all the active assembly relationships and properties and is a convenient wrapper around the functionality of PSRelationshipProcessorProxy with methods that are meaningful for active assembly processing.

Active assembly involves manipultion of item (owner), variant, slot and relationship objects based on some preconfigured rules.

An implementor should be able to achieve everything he wants to do around active assembly using this class. He can use the class PSRelationshipProcessorProxy and do the same, however, it will be more work.

Author:
RammohanVangapalli

                                                 PSSlotType slot,
                                                 int authType)
                                          throws PSCmsException
Get the list of all relationships for the given slot of the item specified by the locator. This is equivalent to getting all related items in the specified slot for manipulation.

Parameters:
owner - Locator for the owner item, must not be null.
slot - item slot object for which the relationships are to be fetched, must not be null.
authType - authorization type value to filter the relationships, one of the valid authorization type valuess. This auth type must have been implemented in sys_casSupport application. It is an error if the requested auth type is not implemented.
Returns:
a sorted list of relationship objects associated with this slot of the item. The list is in the order of sort rank property of the relationships. It is never null, may be empty.
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if the item locator or the slot supplied is null or slotid specified is invalid.
PSCmsException - if it cannot extract relationships for the item slot for any reason.

reArrangeSlotRelationships

public void reArrangeSlotRelationships(PSAaRelationshipList slotRelations,
                                       int index)
                                throws PSCmsException
Rearrange the related items specified via relationships and move to a specified location. All the items from the relationship list will be arranged together in the order they occur in the set and moved to the specified location. The first item (relationship) in the list will get the order specified by the new location. Specify 0 to move to top in the slot and -1 (or a value larger than the items in the slot) to move to bottom. All relationships in the list must be for the same slot and have the same owner.

Parameters:
slotRelations - list of relationships to rearrange and move, must not be null or empty.
index - new location, -1 for bottom and any other value specified becomes the sort index of the first item in the relationship list to rearrange.
Throws:
PSCmsException - if rearrange fails for any reason.

addSlotRelationships

public void addSlotRelationships(PSAaRelationshipList newSlotRelations,
                                 int locIndex)
                          throws PSCmsException
Add new items specified by the relationship list to a slot at a specified location index. All relationships in the list must be for the same owner and slot for this method to be successful. Also, all the relationships must have an id of -1. The sortrank properties of all saved relationships will be normalized starting with 1, continiously incremented by 1.

Parameters:
newSlotRelations - list of relationships to add at the location specified, must not be null or empty.
locIndex - the location index where to insert the new supplied relationships into existing relationships. Supply -1 or a value greater than the existing relationship size to append the ones to the end.
Throws:
PSCmsException - if add fails for any reason.

removeSlotRelations

                         throws PSCmsException
Remove items specified by the relationship list from a slot. All relationships in the list must have the same owner and for the same slot for this method to be successful.

Parameters:

Throws:

  2. if all relationships are not for the same slot or do not share the same owner
PSCmsException - if remove fails for any reason.
